This is the "separate race" version of the Vampire, where after conversion, all vampires are transformed into the same similar species. For the version that's an addon to existing races, see [[[5e:vampyric| Vampire]]].

+ Vampires
//**Vampires are a uniquely powerful form of undead that were not killed, but converted from life. As children of [[[Noctra]]] they are often chaotic beings, that rely on trickery, magic, and darkness to get their way. Some vampires choose this life, others have it thrust upon them as they are made the pawn of a greater entity, but all of them consume blood to survive. **//
* **Ability Score Increase.** Your Charisma score increases by 2.

* **Age.** Vampires do not age after the point of their conversion.

* **Alignment.**  Vampires might not have an innate tendency toward evil, but many of them end up there. Evil or not, an independent nature inclines many vampires toward a chaotic alignment.

* **Size.** Vampires are about the same size and build as humans. Your size is Medium.

* **Speed.** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

* **Darkvision.** Thanks to your nocturnal heritage, you have superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You can see in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light, and in darkness as if it were dim light. You can’t discern color in darkness, only shades of gray.

* **Immortal Tricksters.** You have advantage on saving throws against being charmed, and magic can't put you to sleep.

* **Siphon.** You have access to the [Vampiric Siphon] cantrip.

* **Trance.** Vampires do not sleep. Instead they meditate deeply, remaining semi-conscious, for 4 hours a day. The Common word for this meditation is "trance." While meditating, you dream after a fashion; such dreams are actually mental exercises that have become reflexive after years of practice. After resting in this way, you gain the same benefit a human would from 8 hours of sleep.

* **Sunlight Sensitivity.** You have disadvantage on attack rolls and Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight when you, the target of the attack, or whatever you are trying to perceive is in direct sunlight. You take 1d4 damage every time you end your turn in direct sunlight.

* **Necrotic Resistance.** You have resistance to necrotic damage.

* **Languages.** You can speak, read, and write Common and Deep Speech.

++ Arcane Tricksters
**//Placeholder.//**

* **Ability Score Increase.** Your Dexterity score increases by 1.

* **Smoke and Mirrors.** You know the [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:thaumaturgy Thaumaturgy] cantrip. Once you reach 3rd level, you can cast the [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:disguise-self Disguise Self] spell once as a 2nd-level spell. Once you reach 5th level, you can also cast the [http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:misty-step Misty Step] spell once. You must finish a long rest to cast these spells again with this trait. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for these spells.

++ Sanguivores 
While regular food and water can partially sustain you temporarily, you must consume the blood of living creatures to survive. More pacifistic vampires will tend to feast on animals and small game, where more jaded or violent vampires are much more likely to consume human blood directly. However, consuming the blood of sapient creatures is far more effective than smaller creatures or animals, and as such a vampire's diet does not necessarily dictate a certain alignment. Once per short rest, you can add 1d6 to any damage roll or ability check, as long as you have consumed the blood of a sapient creature within the past 24 hours. 
If you have not consumed the blood of any living creatures in the past 24 hours, your movement is halved. After 48 hours, subtract 1d4 from all attack rolls, ability checks, and saving throws. 



